Python Control Flow :
Title: Flight distance calculator 

Concept:
Great-circle distance = the shortest path between two points on Earth (used in flight routing).

Formula:
d=R×arccos(sin(lat1)sin(lat2)+cos(lat1)cos(lat2)cos(lon2−lon1))

where R = Earth’s radius (≈ 6371 km or 3440 NM).
Estimated Time of Flight (EET) = Distance ÷ Ground Speed.

Tech used :
Language : pyhton
Compiler : Visual Studio Code

Logic Flow:
- Fetch coordinates automatically via ICAO codes (using API)
- Add ground speed variation (winds aloft)
- Integrate map visualization with `matplotlib` or `geopy`	
